The paper focuses on a minimalist kernel for computation of linear and relational algebra, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses optimization rules and efficient implementations, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper presents an implementation in Apache Accumulo, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) topic.
